WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:05.967 --> 00:00:09.471
This intelligence unit
is hereby disbanded.

2
00:00:10.049 --> 00:00:11.968
I'll get your badge.

3
00:00:12.052 --> 00:00:14.233
You just haven't
accepted it yet.

4
00:00:14.317 --> 00:00:17.821
Your team's badges.
they're already mine.

5
00:00:19.590 --> 00:00:21.884
-Gun!
-Gun! Take cover!

6
00:00:24.014 --> 00:00:26.975
They're continuing their
investigation into our unit.

7
00:00:27.059 --> 00:00:29.187
So it's... it's over?

8
00:00:29.308 --> 00:00:31.519
We'll have to wait and see.

9
00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:39.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

10
00:01:25.919 --> 00:01:27.837
[grunts softly

11
00:01:41.685 --> 00:01:43.603
Morning.

12
00:01:43.687 --> 00:01:46.690
Word is IAD Commander Devlin's
out of the office today

13
00:01:46.773 --> 00:01:49.275
because he's attending the
Gold Star Memorial donor event.

14
00:01:49.442 --> 00:01:50.819
Mm.

15
00:01:50.985 --> 00:01:52.738
He'll be there all morning.
then be shaking hands

16
00:01:52.821 --> 00:01:54.489
and taking donors
out until sundown.

17
00:01:54.572 --> 00:01:56.199
I say you catch him beforehand.

18
00:01:56.324 --> 00:01:57.951
Mm-hmm.

19
00:01:58.118 --> 00:02:00.036
Maybe find a few more
syllables by then.

20
00:02:00.120 --> 00:02:01.246
some complete sentences.

21
00:02:01.329 --> 00:02:02.706
Okay.

22
00:02:02.831 --> 00:02:05.041
-You want me to go with you?
-No.

23
00:02:05.125 --> 00:02:08.003
The man is risk-averse.
politically minded.

24
00:02:08.086 --> 00:02:09.796
He does not respond to pressure.

25
00:02:09.879 --> 00:02:12.173
I know who he is.
It's been a month.

26
00:02:12.257 --> 00:02:15.218
-Oh. look. it finds its voice.
-Yes. it does.

27
00:02:15.385 --> 00:02:16.928
And it's going to be fine.

28
00:02:17.012 --> 00:02:19.556
so you got to stop checking
on it. bringing it coffee.

29
00:02:19.639 --> 00:02:21.558
I don't come here.
I don't see you.

30
00:02:21.641 --> 00:02:23.184
The team is scattered.

31
00:02:23.309 --> 00:02:26.604
I know Chapman isn't speaking
to you. so somebody has to.

32
00:02:26.688 --> 00:02:28.148
Trudy. I'm good.

33
00:02:28.231 --> 00:02:30.734
Look. today's the day. right?
-Mm-hmm.

34
00:02:30.900 --> 00:02:33.111
Donor event at the wall?

35
00:02:33.194 --> 00:02:34.988
Come on.
-Here.

36
00:03:02.432 --> 00:03:04.768
-Hank.
-Sir.

37
00:03:04.851 --> 00:03:07.354
-You missed a lovely event.
-Huh.

38
00:03:08.980 --> 00:03:10.649
It's officially been four weeks.

39
00:03:10.732 --> 00:03:12.067
Full breakfast. nice speeches.

40
00:03:12.150 --> 00:03:13.777
They even mentioned your father.

41
00:03:13.860 --> 00:03:14.944
You should have attended.

42
00:03:15.028 --> 00:03:16.405
That's a full month

43
00:03:16.488 --> 00:03:18.948
since the Intelligence
Unit has been disbanded.

44
00:03:19.032 --> 00:03:20.867
My team's all been on
their best behavior.

45
00:03:20.950 --> 00:03:23.286
Every charge of misconduct
has been dismissed.

46
00:03:23.411 --> 00:03:24.954
I know.

47
00:03:25.080 --> 00:03:27.207
The only thing left is for you
to sign on the dotted line.

48
00:03:27.290 --> 00:03:29.584
reinstate us.
-I know.

49
00:03:32.253 --> 00:03:34.798
My officer Kiana Cook...

50
00:03:34.881 --> 00:03:38.510
she just took a permanent
spot in the 17th.

51
00:03:38.593 --> 00:03:40.595
I don't want to lose
any more members.

52
00:03:40.679 --> 00:03:42.472
I can sympathize.

53
00:03:42.555 --> 00:03:45.017
I need them to know we're back.

54
00:03:45.100 --> 00:03:48.812
Well. they're
gonna have to wait.

55
00:03:48.895 --> 00:03:51.648
Sir...

56
00:03:51.773 --> 00:03:54.109
I'm sure I don't
need to tell you

57
00:03:54.192 --> 00:03:57.112
there's been a steady
uptick in crime...

58
00:03:57.195 --> 00:04:00.949
9% rise in homicide.
22% in gun violence.

59
00:04:01.032 --> 00:04:04.244
I can relate that directly
to my team being benched.

60
00:04:04.369 --> 00:04:07.122
You're right. You don't
need to tell me that.

61
00:04:09.165 --> 00:04:11.209
I was promised a
four-week evaluation.

62
00:04:11.334 --> 00:04:14.796
No. you were told a four-week
evaluation at minimum.

63
00:04:14.879 --> 00:04:16.631
I need more time.

64
00:04:19.509 --> 00:04:20.427
How much?

65
00:04:23.179 --> 00:04:25.432
I don't relish this. Hank.

66
00:04:25.515 --> 00:04:27.350
And if you want to
talk consequences.

67
00:04:27.517 --> 00:04:30.645
I believe these are yours.

68
00:04:30.729 --> 00:04:32.272
I was given this responsibility.

69
00:04:32.397 --> 00:04:34.942
and I don't take it lightly.
-It's just a signature.

70
00:04:35.025 --> 00:04:38.820
No. it's my signature.
my name on your unit.

71
00:04:38.903 --> 00:04:40.655
Think about that.

72
00:04:43.366 --> 00:04:47.162
You just keep working
Rapid Response.

73
00:04:47.328 --> 00:04:48.955
I need more time.

74
00:06:00.443 --> 00:06:02.362
Damn it.

75
00:06:06.199 --> 00:06:08.410
I got to go.
-Yeah.

76
00:06:10.954 --> 00:06:14.249
15's got me working
Parkers and movers today.

77
00:06:14.332 --> 00:06:17.002
So. you know. one
simply cannot be late.

78
00:06:17.085 --> 00:06:20.171
Yeah. well. at least
it's something.

79
00:06:20.255 --> 00:06:21.673
Sorry. honey.

80
00:06:23.967 --> 00:06:25.385
Voight's meeting with
Commander Devlin today.

81
00:06:25.468 --> 00:06:27.137
You and Dante are going
to get your badges back.

82
00:06:27.220 --> 00:06:28.930
I know it.
-Yeah.

83
00:06:30.765 --> 00:06:32.392
You'll be back.

84
00:06:41.151 --> 00:06:44.195
Man. I thought we'd
finally be rid of your ass.

85
00:06:44.320 --> 00:06:46.531
be rid of you bothering
the damn neighborhood.

86
00:06:46.656 --> 00:06:48.533
Day in. day out. not
minding your business.

87
00:06:48.658 --> 00:06:50.202
-Keep digging.
-There ain't nothing in here.

88
00:06:50.285 --> 00:06:51.494
-Keep digging.
-Never was.

89
00:06:51.619 --> 00:06:53.747
Why don't you dig
over there? Dig.

90
00:06:53.872 --> 00:06:56.291
I'm telling you.
you're wasting your...

91
00:06:56.374 --> 00:06:58.168
I knew it. What did I tell you?

92
00:06:58.251 --> 00:07:00.503
What did I say?
-Dig 'em out. Dig 'em out!

93
00:07:00.587 --> 00:07:01.963
Watch out for those peppers.

94
00:07:02.088 --> 00:07:04.049
I ain't touching
your damn plants.

95
00:07:04.132 --> 00:07:06.009
-All of them.
-Oh. you want to swear at me?

96
00:07:06.092 --> 00:07:07.761
Here's a thought. Ludo.

97
00:07:07.844 --> 00:07:10.055
Don't hide your jab in
your auntie's garden.

98
00:07:10.180 --> 00:07:11.515
I find out you stash
here...

99
00:07:11.598 --> 00:07:13.725
-Oh!
-Hey. stay low.

100
00:07:13.808 --> 00:07:15.143
Stay low.

101
00:07:16.686 --> 00:07:18.521
1140. squad.

102
00:07:18.605 --> 00:07:20.523
I
got shots fired.

103
00:07:20.648 --> 00:07:22.567
4200 Keeler in the alley.

104
00:07:22.692 --> 00:07:24.486
Roll some units. I'm
responding on foot.

105
00:07:26.654 --> 00:07:28.490
I got shots fired. 4200 Keeler.

106
00:07:28.573 --> 00:07:30.283
Want to stay off the air.

107
00:07:32.994 --> 00:07:36.331
1140. squad. I need an
ambo. I got one down.

108
00:07:36.414 --> 00:07:39.125
Copy. 1140.

109
00:07:39.292 --> 00:07:40.960
Hey!

110
00:07:41.086 --> 00:07:42.379
Chicago PD!

111
00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:43.838
Drop your weapon! Drop it!

112
00:07:51.221 --> 00:07:53.056
Offender fleeing
eastbound on Crenshaw.

113
00:07:53.181 --> 00:07:54.516
Help! Help me!

114
00:07:54.599 --> 00:07:56.226
He's in a brown Ford. no plate.

115
00:07:56.351 --> 00:07:57.894
His front passenger
tire is blown out.

116
00:07:58.019 --> 00:07:59.854
Sarge! Sarge! Any more
offenders on scene?

117
00:07:59.979 --> 00:08:02.149
No! Cover that DOA right there!

118
00:08:02.232 --> 00:08:04.275
Don't let anyone near him!
-Copy that.

119
00:08:04.401 --> 00:08:07.904
It's a male. Black.
5'9". 180 pounds.

120
00:08:07.987 --> 00:08:10.615
He's heavily armed.
-Help! Help me!

121
00:08:10.699 --> 00:08:11.908
Somebody!

122
00:08:14.077 --> 00:08:16.121
1140. I need that ambo now.

123
00:08:16.204 --> 00:08:18.290
10-4. 1140. Ambo's en route.

124
00:08:18.373 --> 00:08:21.418
Go get some rags.
Go get some rags.

125
00:08:24.713 --> 00:08:27.966
Come on. Aggie. I
need you to fight.

126
00:08:28.049 --> 00:08:29.926
Come on. come on. Fight. Aggie.

127
00:08:41.354 --> 00:08:43.180
Here. I brought
everything I could find.

128
00:08:43.264 --> 00:08:45.705
Good. Here. press hard on
those two wounds right there.

129
00:08:45.789 --> 00:08:47.958
Harder than that.
Harder than you want to.

130
00:08:48.042 --> 00:08:49.922
You're not going to
hurt her. you hear me?

131
00:08:50.006 --> 00:08:51.967
Press
hard. Good. There you go.

132
00:08:52.051 --> 00:08:53.511
She's bleeding too
much. isn't she?

133
00:08:53.595 --> 00:08:55.953
Stay with me. Aggie. I
need you to be strong.

134
00:08:56.036 --> 00:08:57.662
Come on.

135
00:08:57.787 --> 00:09:00.123
Come on.

136
00:09:03.043 --> 00:09:04.169
Whoa! What are you doing?

137
00:09:04.294 --> 00:09:06.421
It'll stop the bleeding for now.

138
00:09:06.504 --> 00:09:08.423
Come on. Aggie. stay with me.
-Is she breathing?

139
00:09:08.506 --> 00:09:09.946
It doesn't seem like
she's breathing.

140
00:09:10.050 --> 00:09:11.968
Aggie? Auntie Aggie.
can you hear me?

141
00:09:12.052 --> 00:09:13.095
-Press hard.
-What we got?

142
00:09:13.178 --> 00:09:14.679
Okay. three shots.

143
00:09:14.763 --> 00:09:16.348
Two through-and-through.
third no exit.

144
00:09:16.431 --> 00:09:18.267
-She's not breathing. is she?
-Pulse is real weak.

145
00:09:18.350 --> 00:09:20.852
Okay. we got her. You
can release your finger.

146
00:09:20.977 --> 00:09:23.021
Sergeant Voight.
release your finger.

147
00:09:23.104 --> 00:09:25.148
-You can stay with her. okay?
-Yeah.

148
00:09:25.273 --> 00:09:26.692
You're doing real good. Ludo.

149
00:09:26.775 --> 00:09:28.651
Hey. he can ride
with you. right?

150
00:09:28.735 --> 00:09:30.653
-Yeah. he can.
-Keep me updated. Brenda.

151
00:09:30.779 --> 00:09:32.739
Will do.

152
00:09:32.822 --> 00:09:34.449
Sir! Hey. sir. back up!

153
00:09:34.574 --> 00:09:35.617
Don't touch him!

154
00:09:35.742 --> 00:09:36.951
Don't!

155
00:09:37.077 --> 00:09:38.620
Hey. I ordered you
to hold the scene.

156
00:09:38.703 --> 00:09:39.954
What the hell are you doing?

157
00:09:40.080 --> 00:09:42.665
Sector Sergeant
wanted me on tape.

158
00:09:42.749 --> 00:09:44.834
Sir. back up. please.
Back up right now.

159
00:09:44.959 --> 00:09:46.044
-I was just trying to help.
-I understand.

160
00:09:46.127 --> 00:09:48.213
I need you to back
off right now. okay?

161
00:09:48.296 --> 00:09:50.424
It's a crime scene.
All the way back.

162
00:09:50.507 --> 00:09:51.549
Thank you.

163
00:09:51.633 --> 00:09:53.510
You got to stay behind the tape.

164
00:10:07.899 --> 00:10:10.318
Hey. we got eyes on that Ford?

165
00:10:10.402 --> 00:10:12.696
No. sir. Sector Sergeant
terminated the chase.

166
00:10:12.821 --> 00:10:13.905
My God.

167
00:10:18.827 --> 00:10:21.413
His tire was blown out.
We could have had him.

168
00:10:21.496 --> 00:10:23.289
Hank.

169
00:10:23.373 --> 00:10:25.208
All right. victim's
ID'd as Kenton Williams.

170
00:10:25.291 --> 00:10:27.002
This is likely his
Acura right here.

171
00:10:27.127 --> 00:10:28.837
-You were first on scene?
-Yeah.

172
00:10:28.962 --> 00:10:31.214
Man died with a Glock and
dummy cash in his hand.

173
00:10:31.339 --> 00:10:33.592
so I'm guessing it's a
dope deal gone wrong.

174
00:10:33.675 --> 00:10:35.677
And this alley is known for it.

175
00:10:35.760 --> 00:10:38.388
Lack of cams. easy
access to 290.

176
00:10:38.513 --> 00:10:39.931
Okay. thanks.

177
00:10:40.015 --> 00:10:42.100
I doubt this offender is
new to the neighborhood.

178
00:10:42.183 --> 00:10:44.352
I got good eyes on
him. I can ID him.

179
00:10:44.436 --> 00:10:46.354
I mean. we should
knock and talk.

180
00:10:48.481 --> 00:10:49.858
The faster. the better.

181
00:10:49.941 --> 00:10:52.861
Well. I talked to
Commander Devlin.

182
00:10:52.944 --> 00:10:54.404
Look. I'd love it
if Intelligence

183
00:10:54.529 --> 00:10:55.447
could work on this one.

184
00:10:55.572 --> 00:10:57.198
Well. I'm standing right here.

185
00:10:57.282 --> 00:10:59.242
But you can't. all right?

186
00:10:59.325 --> 00:11:00.827
And I'm not stepping
between you and Devlin.

187
00:11:00.910 --> 00:11:02.370
I-I don't want any of that.

188
00:11:02.454 --> 00:11:06.041
You were only assigned to
work in-progress calls.

189
00:11:06.124 --> 00:11:07.375
Here you go.

190
00:11:07.459 --> 00:11:09.919
I recovered it
off the dead body.

191
00:11:10.045 --> 00:11:12.547
The other gun was a fully auto.

192
00:11:12.630 --> 00:11:14.966
so we got another
on our streets.

193
00:11:15.091 --> 00:11:16.593
I'm sorry. Hank.

194
00:11:19.387 --> 00:11:21.264
No. no. no. tape first.

195
00:11:21.389 --> 00:11:24.142
All right. call Forensics.
Hold the scene. all right?

196
00:11:24.225 --> 00:11:26.227
Slow and steady.

197
00:11:44.913 --> 00:11:47.833
Yo! Jos!

198
00:11:47.916 --> 00:11:50.877
You see that car
just drove past here?

199
00:11:50.960 --> 00:11:54.422
Six minutes ago... beater
brown Ford. flat tire.

200
00:11:54.506 --> 00:11:57.384
Black male driver. 20s. 30s.

201
00:11:57.467 --> 00:11:58.844
You know his name?

202
00:12:01.388 --> 00:12:03.181
Hey! Yo! Yo!

203
00:12:03.264 --> 00:12:05.141
Hank. stop. yo!

204
00:12:05.266 --> 00:12:07.102
Hey. what's your problem?

205
00:12:07.185 --> 00:12:09.020
Tell me who the driver is.

206
00:12:09.104 --> 00:12:10.814
I'm sitting here
minding my business.

207
00:12:10.897 --> 00:12:12.524
Bro. I know for a fact

208
00:12:12.607 --> 00:12:14.401
you got at least
two jabs of work

209
00:12:14.526 --> 00:12:16.611
and two girls in
there right now.

210
00:12:16.736 --> 00:12:18.071
Now. you want that
to be your day.

211
00:12:18.196 --> 00:12:20.573
or you want to tell
me who the driver is?

212
00:12:20.657 --> 00:12:22.784
-I-I don't know his name.
-That ain't helpful.

213
00:12:25.495 --> 00:12:28.707
B-b-b-but I-I seen
him and his ride.

214
00:12:28.790 --> 00:12:29.833
Uh-huh.

215
00:12:29.916 --> 00:12:32.127
H-he hang at Mondo's.

216
00:12:32.210 --> 00:12:33.545
I-I seen him there.

217
00:12:41.219 --> 00:12:45.933
Victim has multiple counts
of PCS. delivery. UUW.

218
00:12:46.016 --> 00:12:48.852
It all fits with a
dope deal gone wrong.

219
00:12:48.935 --> 00:12:51.980
Yeah. Victim tried to stiff
our offender. got shot for it.

220
00:12:52.063 --> 00:12:54.482
Okay. wait. Did you
get word from Devlin?

221
00:12:54.566 --> 00:12:55.942
Are we back?

222
00:12:56.067 --> 00:12:59.988
Look. it's another
DOA from a fully auto.

223
00:13:00.113 --> 00:13:02.658
I mean. sector has failed
on five bodies this month.

224
00:13:02.741 --> 00:13:03.867
It's enough.

225
00:13:03.950 --> 00:13:06.077
Adam. I got a witness.

226
00:13:06.202 --> 00:13:09.205
He recognized our shooter.
He's seen him at a local bar.

227
00:13:09.330 --> 00:13:11.291
Can you bum off for an
hour and meet me there?

228
00:13:11.416 --> 00:13:13.501
We're not back. are we?

229
00:13:13.626 --> 00:13:14.711
No.

230
00:13:14.836 --> 00:13:16.087
All right. what bar?

231
00:13:16.212 --> 00:13:19.507
Mondo's. Its 18th and Hamlin.

232
00:13:39.486 --> 00:13:41.404
Yo. man. Hey. you
work here a lot?

233
00:13:41.529 --> 00:13:43.073
What's a lot?

234
00:13:43.198 --> 00:13:44.783
I was in here with my
guys a few nights back.

235
00:13:44.866 --> 00:13:46.368
I had my ride parked out front.

236
00:13:46.451 --> 00:13:47.952
Brown Ford ripped right into it.

237
00:13:48.078 --> 00:13:49.412
took the bumper clean off.

238
00:13:49.496 --> 00:13:51.415
I got. like. $500
worth of damages.

239
00:13:51.498 --> 00:13:52.999
I don't
work the streets.

240
00:13:53.124 --> 00:13:55.377
I get that. I mean.
clearly. it came from here.

241
00:13:55.460 --> 00:13:58.505
I just need a name.
-Don't got one.

242
00:13:58.588 --> 00:14:00.799
Come on. man. a-a brown
Ford. beat to hell.

243
00:14:00.882 --> 00:14:02.926
It's real hard to
miss. Black driver.

244
00:14:03.009 --> 00:14:04.427
Yeah. I don't know.

245
00:14:09.766 --> 00:14:11.267
Yeah. I don't want no trouble.

246
00:14:11.393 --> 00:14:13.353
I know. but I'm not going to
tell him where I got the name.

247
00:14:13.436 --> 00:14:16.022
I just need a name.
-I... but... no. man.

248
00:14:16.106 --> 00:14:17.899
What kind of car are
you asking about?

249
00:14:18.024 --> 00:14:19.359
What's that?

250
00:14:19.484 --> 00:14:21.737
I said. what kind of car
are you asking about?

251
00:14:21.820 --> 00:14:22.821
Yo. stop.

252
00:14:22.946 --> 00:14:24.447
Look. I don't want no trouble.

253
00:14:24.531 --> 00:14:26.449
Brown Ford. Black
driver... you know him?

254
00:14:26.574 --> 00:14:27.826
Why you asking?

255
00:14:27.909 --> 00:14:29.828
Well. he hit my car.
took off. hit-and-run.

256
00:14:29.911 --> 00:14:31.079
-Hit-and-run. huh?
-Yeah.

257
00:14:31.204 --> 00:14:33.164
Yo. Dee. stop.

258
00:14:33.289 --> 00:14:34.708
I ain't never seen
you in here before.

259
00:14:34.791 --> 00:14:36.001
No. Hey.

260
00:14:36.084 --> 00:14:38.420
Never seen you before either.

261
00:14:38.503 --> 00:14:39.796
That ain't the same.

262
00:14:39.879 --> 00:14:41.881
Dee. stop. Leave it alone.

263
00:14:41.965 --> 00:14:43.508
-Look. man.
-Come on.

264
00:14:43.591 --> 00:14:45.844
-I don't know you.
-Dee. calm down. Sit...

265
00:14:45.927 --> 00:14:48.138
I don't know your car that
got clipped out front.

266
00:14:48.221 --> 00:14:49.723
Why you in here asking
about a brown Ford?

267
00:14:49.806 --> 00:14:50.849
I just told you.

268
00:14:50.932 --> 00:14:52.434
Now. see. I don't
like that answer.

269
00:14:52.517 --> 00:14:54.186
-Let it go. Dee. hey. stop.
-We're not doing this again.

270
00:14:54.269 --> 00:14:55.854
-I don't like that answer.
-Stop! Stop! No!

271
00:14:55.937 --> 00:14:57.605
Yo. yo. yo. I don't
want no trouble.

272
00:14:57.689 --> 00:14:59.149
I'm just asking about a car.

273
00:14:59.232 --> 00:15:00.942
See. you not just
asking. Not when you...

274
00:15:01.026 --> 00:15:02.819
Come on. come on! Yo. Dee. hey!

275
00:15:02.944 --> 00:15:04.654
Hey!

276
00:15:04.738 --> 00:15:06.239
Yo. Dee. get... get out of here!
-That's what you want to do?

277
00:15:06.322 --> 00:15:07.407
-Get out.
-Huh?

278
00:15:07.490 --> 00:15:09.117
Come get this. Come on.
-Dee. get. Run.

279
00:15:14.748 --> 00:15:15.957
-Go!
-I remember faces.

280
00:15:16.041 --> 00:15:19.127
-Run!
-I see you. I'ma get you.

281
00:15:24.299 --> 00:15:26.843
Son of a bitch.

282
00:15:26.926 --> 00:15:29.262
I'm police. all right?

283
00:15:29.387 --> 00:15:32.140
So put the bottle
down now. Put it down.

284
00:15:33.725 --> 00:15:36.770
God damn it.

285
00:15:36.853 --> 00:15:39.189
Hey! Stop!

286
00:15:41.816 --> 00:15:44.819
Stop. stop. stop. Hey.
Stop. Would you stop?

287
00:15:44.944 --> 00:15:46.529
Get...

288
00:15:49.032 --> 00:15:52.369
Police! Stop struggling!

289
00:15:54.662 --> 00:15:57.374
Put down the gun. you idiot.
I'm on duty with the ATF.

290
00:16:05.498 --> 00:16:08.102
ATF down with you shivving
officers with beer bottles?

291
00:16:08.186 --> 00:16:10.430
-Can we make this quicker?
-Who drives that Ford?

292
00:16:10.514 --> 00:16:11.627
Why you want to know?

293
00:16:11.711 --> 00:16:13.782
That's not how it
works. You answer first.

294
00:16:13.866 --> 00:16:15.271
I got no idea who
drives it. all right?

295
00:16:15.355 --> 00:16:17.519
I've never seen it. but.
clearly. my contact has.

296
00:16:17.602 --> 00:16:18.729
Why do you want to know?

297
00:16:18.812 --> 00:16:20.564
Because the driver
just killed a man

298
00:16:20.647 --> 00:16:24.317
and his 75-year-old
grandmother with a Draco Mini.

299
00:16:24.401 --> 00:16:26.444
-When?
-This morning.

300
00:16:26.528 --> 00:16:28.321
It looked like a
dope deal gone wrong.

301
00:16:28.446 --> 00:16:30.240
Now I'm assuming
it was a gun deal.

302
00:16:30.323 --> 00:16:32.826
Are you working a gunrunner?
-I'm trying to.

303
00:16:32.909 --> 00:16:34.786
Who?

304
00:16:34.869 --> 00:16:37.164
Look. chances are we're
chasing the same guy.

305
00:16:37.247 --> 00:16:39.082
I don't got to tell a beat
sergeant what I'm working.

306
00:16:39.165 --> 00:16:41.084
-Excuse me?
-Did I stutter?

307
00:16:41.167 --> 00:16:43.753
I don't need to
tell you. all right?

308
00:16:43.837 --> 00:16:45.005
I got to go right now.

309
00:16:45.088 --> 00:16:47.090
So you got my name.
You have all my info.

310
00:16:47.173 --> 00:16:48.591
You can run it up
to your superiors.

311
00:16:48.675 --> 00:16:50.093
Give me my ID.

312
00:16:50.176 --> 00:16:52.345
No.

313
00:16:52.429 --> 00:16:54.056
Look. my boss will
tell your superiors

314
00:16:54.139 --> 00:16:55.515
what I'm working. all right?

315
00:16:55.598 --> 00:16:57.225
They'll give you
everything. Give me my ID.

316
00:16:57.308 --> 00:16:59.144
I got to go.

317
00:16:59.227 --> 00:17:01.312
She's right. Let her have it.

318
00:17:07.027 --> 00:17:08.737
Hey. what are we doing?

319
00:17:13.408 --> 00:17:15.243
All right. so what's happening?

320
00:17:15.326 --> 00:17:18.288
Well. I'm not gonna wait
to run it through systems.

321
00:17:18.371 --> 00:17:19.581
Just follow her.

322
00:17:19.664 --> 00:17:21.416
All right. boss.
what's going on?

323
00:17:21.499 --> 00:17:23.251
I thought the plan
was to lay low.

324
00:17:23.376 --> 00:17:25.837
swallow the consequences
until Devlin signs us back.

325
00:17:25.920 --> 00:17:28.298
He's not signing us back yet.

326
00:17:28.381 --> 00:17:29.758
Yet or ever?

327
00:17:36.723 --> 00:17:38.767
-Come on. we got to go.
-Boss. I just...

328
00:17:38.850 --> 00:17:40.935
I can't be away from
my beat this long.

329
00:17:42.645 --> 00:17:44.356
Fine. I got it.

330
00:18:26.106 --> 00:18:27.315
Sarge?

331
00:18:27.440 --> 00:18:29.025
What are you doing right now?

332
00:18:29.109 --> 00:18:30.277
Um...

333
00:18:30.360 --> 00:18:31.361
uh. nothing.

334
00:18:31.486 --> 00:18:33.113
I'm not doing anything.

335
00:18:33.238 --> 00:18:35.616
We back?
-I need a favor.

336
00:18:35.699 --> 00:18:37.409
It'll be off-book.

337
00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:41.413
Can you meet me ASAP?

338
00:18:43.456 --> 00:18:45.166
Kim?

339
00:18:45.291 --> 00:18:47.669
Yeah. Yeah.

340
00:18:47.752 --> 00:18:49.421
I'll leave right now.

341
00:18:49.504 --> 00:18:52.924
She's still on Cermak.
changing lanes.

342
00:18:53.008 --> 00:18:55.844
Copy you. I'm headed
southbound on Holman.

343
00:18:55.969 --> 00:18:58.430
-Copy.
-All right. just stay wide.

344
00:18:58.513 --> 00:19:01.516
I'll call you back in two.
-Got it.

345
00:19:01.599 --> 00:19:03.059
What happened with Devlin?

346
00:19:03.184 --> 00:19:05.645
Trudy. you know anything
about a female CPD officer

347
00:19:05.729 --> 00:19:08.064
detailed to ATF named Eva Imani?

348
00:19:08.148 --> 00:19:09.357
That's my answer?

349
00:19:09.441 --> 00:19:11.901
Spelled I-M-A-N-I.

350
00:19:11.985 --> 00:19:13.570
Yeah. I heard of her.

351
00:19:13.695 --> 00:19:15.530
She was detailed straight
out of the academy.

352
00:19:15.613 --> 00:19:16.990
Never heard so many stories

353
00:19:17.073 --> 00:19:18.742
about someone making
so few friends.

354
00:19:18.867 --> 00:19:20.201
Why?
-I got to go.

355
00:19:20.326 --> 00:19:21.661
Yeah.

356
00:19:21.786 --> 00:19:23.663
I've got her
curbing the vehicle.

357
00:19:28.752 --> 00:19:31.046
Okay. she's approaching...

358
00:19:31.129 --> 00:19:33.048
Where the hell you been?
I've been calling you.

359
00:19:33.131 --> 00:19:34.924
3545 Christina.

360
00:19:35.008 --> 00:19:37.177
I got a male. Black. late 20s.

361
00:19:37.260 --> 00:19:39.012
He's on the front porch.
-Headed to you.

362
00:19:39.095 --> 00:19:40.805
Sounds like her
contact from the bar.

363
00:19:45.894 --> 00:19:47.896
Address is listed
to her fake ID.

364
00:19:47.979 --> 00:19:50.482
It must be a UC apartment.

365
00:19:50.565 --> 00:19:52.442
They're entering now.

366
00:19:55.862 --> 00:19:57.572
I'm going to do a walk-by.

367
00:19:57.655 --> 00:20:00.325
Copy. Stay wide.
Stay on the line.

368
00:20:03.370 --> 00:20:05.288
Mm-hmm.

369
00:20:22.514 --> 00:20:23.682
Sarge. this woman
have backup inside?

370
00:20:23.765 --> 00:20:24.933
I don't know.

371
00:20:25.016 --> 00:20:26.935
Cop shows up asking
about Raptor's car

372
00:20:27.018 --> 00:20:28.520
two weeks after
your ass appears.

373
00:20:28.645 --> 00:20:29.771
wanting to know me.

374
00:20:29.896 --> 00:20:31.481
wanting to know
how I make scratch.

375
00:20:31.564 --> 00:20:32.857
wanting me to scratch you back?

376
00:20:32.941 --> 00:20:34.442
And now this is all
in my head. bitch?

377
00:20:34.526 --> 00:20:36.403
What the hell is wrong with you?

378
00:20:36.528 --> 00:20:39.239
What the hell is wrong with me?

379
00:20:39.322 --> 00:20:42.534
I think she's been made.

380
00:20:42.617 --> 00:20:44.494
This girl's in
trouble. I'm going in.

381
00:20:47.664 --> 00:20:49.166
Let her go.

382
00:20:49.249 --> 00:20:50.417
Listen to me. I
said. let her go.

383
00:20:50.500 --> 00:20:51.793
Shut up!

384
00:20:51.918 --> 00:20:53.712
Chicago PD!

385
00:20:53.795 --> 00:20:56.339
Get off of her!

386
00:20:56.423 --> 00:20:58.008
Get off!

387
00:21:09.811 --> 00:21:11.730
Go! You got to move.

388
00:21:11.813 --> 00:21:14.274
You got to get out.
Go! You got to go!

389
00:21:31.394 --> 00:21:32.959
Jesus.

390
00:21:34.133 --> 00:21:35.209
Kim. you got to go.

391
00:21:35.293 --> 00:21:38.382
He was going to kill
her. so I had to move.

392
00:21:38.465 --> 00:21:39.758
You're not on the job.

393
00:21:39.841 --> 00:21:41.400
You got to go.
-God damn it.

394
00:21:41.484 --> 00:21:44.404
I know.

395
00:21:44.846 --> 00:21:46.514
I know.

396
00:21:51.311 --> 00:21:52.771
She was never here.

397
00:21:52.854 --> 00:21:55.023
-What?
-She was never here.

398
00:21:55.148 --> 00:21:56.692
-Who the hell are you?
-Is this his gun?

399
00:21:56.775 --> 00:21:58.610
What kind of patrol sergeant...

400
00:21:58.693 --> 00:21:59.987
Did you follow me here?

401
00:22:00.070 --> 00:22:02.405
Yes.

402
00:22:02.572 --> 00:22:04.449
It would have taken hours
for your boss to give me

403
00:22:04.532 --> 00:22:06.076
the information. which you knew.

404
00:22:06.159 --> 00:22:07.369
so I followed you instead.

405
00:22:07.452 --> 00:22:08.745
You're welcome!

406
00:22:08.828 --> 00:22:11.248
Now. is this his gun?

407
00:22:11.331 --> 00:22:13.000
Is this his gun?
-Yes.

408
00:22:13.083 --> 00:22:14.834
Okay. who is he?

409
00:22:16.503 --> 00:22:17.754
His name is Dee Hart.

410
00:22:17.879 --> 00:22:19.464
He works for a gunrunner
we've been targeting.

411
00:22:19.547 --> 00:22:20.966
Okay. what's the
gunrunner's name?

412
00:22:21.049 --> 00:22:22.300
-I don't know.
-Oh. please.

413
00:22:22.384 --> 00:22:25.679
I don't. Dee only ever
called him Raptor.

414
00:22:25.762 --> 00:22:27.848
Guy hits gun shows.
gun shops. trains.

415
00:22:27.931 --> 00:22:29.725
then sells the pieces
for real cheap.

416
00:22:29.808 --> 00:22:32.018
I've linked his guns to
23 bodies in the Midwest.

417
00:22:32.143 --> 00:22:34.187
Hewas supposed to get me a meet.

418
00:22:34.270 --> 00:22:36.690
Okay. you got a description?

419
00:22:36.773 --> 00:22:39.359
Black male. 5'9".

420
00:22:39.442 --> 00:22:42.195
Yeah. I bet he
drives a brown Ford.

421
00:22:43.947 --> 00:22:45.616
23 bodies.

422
00:22:49.202 --> 00:22:50.495
Hey.

423
00:22:50.578 --> 00:22:53.373
Hey. Hey.

424
00:22:53.456 --> 00:22:56.042
It was just you and
me here. you hear me?

425
00:22:59.546 --> 00:23:01.381
There's a reason
we have protocol.

426
00:23:01.464 --> 00:23:04.050
because protocol prevents
piss-poor police performance.

427
00:23:04.217 --> 00:23:06.011
-Yeah. I know the speech.
-Do you?

428
00:23:06.094 --> 00:23:08.096
Because you didn't call it
in. You didn't have a ghost.

429
00:23:08.179 --> 00:23:10.182
And now I'm looking at a man
with two holes in his head.

430
00:23:10.265 --> 00:23:12.476
-What the hell happened?
-Sir.

431
00:23:12.559 --> 00:23:14.311
I crossed paths with ATF.

432
00:23:14.394 --> 00:23:16.146
Looks like we're
after the same guy.

433
00:23:16.229 --> 00:23:17.689
Offender from this morning

434
00:23:17.772 --> 00:23:19.942
matches an ATF gunrunner target.

435
00:23:20.025 --> 00:23:21.651
Which offender?

436
00:23:21.735 --> 00:23:23.904
11th district.

437
00:23:23.987 --> 00:23:25.864
The offender who
left Kenton Williams

438
00:23:26.031 --> 00:23:27.741
riddled with rounds.

439
00:23:27.824 --> 00:23:30.077
left Aggie Montgomery.
75 years old. dead

440
00:23:30.160 --> 00:23:32.954
from stray bullets
fired from a fully auto.

441
00:23:33.038 --> 00:23:34.247
That offender.

442
00:23:34.330 --> 00:23:36.458
You mean the sector
sergeant's case?

443
00:23:36.541 --> 00:23:38.293
-I caught it in progress.
-How is that possible?

444
00:23:38.376 --> 00:23:41.171
You didn't answer a single
in-progress call all day.

445
00:23:41.296 --> 00:23:42.464
He was on view.

446
00:23:44.090 --> 00:23:46.176
I was working my
contact at Mondo's.

447
00:23:46.259 --> 00:23:48.762
Dee here was acting real shaky.
I didn't like the feeling.

448
00:23:48.845 --> 00:23:50.764
I clocked Sergeant
Voight outside.

449
00:23:50.847 --> 00:23:53.391
asked him discreet
to follow me. alone.

450
00:23:53.475 --> 00:23:56.102
Good thing he did. Dee
had made me as police.

451
00:23:56.227 --> 00:23:58.146
Attacked me as soon as he could.

452
00:23:58.229 --> 00:24:00.107
You know. Dee's death's
still relatively quiet.

453
00:24:00.190 --> 00:24:02.192
You should probably work your
leads before they dry up.

454
00:24:02.275 --> 00:24:03.860
I can help.
-No.

455
00:24:03.943 --> 00:24:05.278
I can use him.

456
00:24:05.362 --> 00:24:06.863
At this point. I don't
care who you use.

457
00:24:06.946 --> 00:24:08.239
as long as you salvage it.

458
00:24:08.323 --> 00:24:10.033
We'll take the scene.
clear up our own mess.

459
00:24:10.116 --> 00:24:12.077
Sorry to have dragged you out.

460
00:24:12.160 --> 00:24:14.662
-Hey.
-Is there a problem?

461
00:24:14.746 --> 00:24:16.331
You want to go against ATF.

462
00:24:16.414 --> 00:24:20.168
let more guns flow onto
our streets. more bodies?

463
00:24:20.251 --> 00:24:23.046
You want to sign
your name to that?

464
00:24:45.193 --> 00:24:46.612
That's Dee's place right there.

465
00:24:46.695 --> 00:24:48.029
Yeah.

466
00:24:49.656 --> 00:24:51.449
Anything in plain view

467
00:24:51.533 --> 00:24:54.411
I've already found
a reason to search.

468
00:24:54.494 --> 00:24:56.496
Dee was real careful
with his crap.

469
00:24:56.579 --> 00:24:58.457
Never left anything with
Raptor's real name sitting out.

470
00:24:58.540 --> 00:25:00.083
How long you been
working Raptor?

471
00:25:00.166 --> 00:25:02.502
Uh. a month.

472
00:25:02.585 --> 00:25:04.462
How many bodies have
his guns dropped

473
00:25:04.546 --> 00:25:07.007
in Chicago in that time?
-Six.

474
00:25:10.552 --> 00:25:12.346
So you going to tell
me who you really are?

475
00:25:12.429 --> 00:25:14.097
Why that IAD commander
hates you so much?

476
00:25:14.222 --> 00:25:16.224
He likes me about as much
as your boss likes you.

477
00:25:16.391 --> 00:25:18.226
Yeah. well. at least
mine's got a reason.

478
00:25:18.393 --> 00:25:20.186
I'm a pain in the
ass. How about yours?

479
00:25:20.270 --> 00:25:22.397
I used to have a unit.
I don't right now.

480
00:25:22.480 --> 00:25:24.608
I'd like him to change that.

481
00:25:24.691 --> 00:25:27.068
Mm. so same answer.

482
00:25:27.193 --> 00:25:29.821
All right. so where
were you before ATF?

483
00:25:29.904 --> 00:25:32.032
Nowhere. everywhere.

484
00:25:32.115 --> 00:25:34.868
Work with PMT. so I
like to keep it moving.

485
00:25:34.951 --> 00:25:36.286
Bingo.

486
00:25:36.369 --> 00:25:38.705
Raptor1239. 9:43 a.m...

487
00:25:38.788 --> 00:25:39.998
"Yo. where you at?

488
00:25:40.081 --> 00:25:42.250
Something popped
off. Get in touch."

489
00:25:44.461 --> 00:25:46.463
We weren't able to
trace the IP address

490
00:25:46.546 --> 00:25:48.257
off the game console.

491
00:25:48.340 --> 00:25:50.425
but we reached out to
Raptor pretending to be Dee.

492
00:25:50.508 --> 00:25:51.801
and it worked.

493
00:25:51.885 --> 00:25:53.887
He told Dee to meet
him there at 9:00 p.m.

494
00:25:53.970 --> 00:25:55.490
We got confirmation
he's our shooter?

495
00:25:55.638 --> 00:25:57.099
ATF did.

496
00:25:57.182 --> 00:25:59.101
Slugs removed from Kenton and
Aggie's bodies were a match

497
00:25:59.184 --> 00:26:01.936
for a Draco Mini that was
suspected stolen by Raptor

498
00:26:02.062 --> 00:26:03.689
out of an Indiana gun
shop six months ago.

499
00:26:03.772 --> 00:26:05.190
It's him.

500
00:26:05.273 --> 00:26:06.984
All right. this
place is desolate.

501
00:26:07.067 --> 00:26:09.194
No cams. no easy access.

502
00:26:09.277 --> 00:26:11.321
So we keep it skeleton. just us.

503
00:26:11.404 --> 00:26:12.906
We got to be on foot.

504
00:26:13.031 --> 00:26:14.407
We got an arrest warrant.

505
00:26:14.491 --> 00:26:17.535
so as soon as Raptor
shows. we grab him up.

506
00:26:17.619 --> 00:26:18.953
Anything?

507
00:26:20.580 --> 00:26:22.457
Nothing yet.

508
00:26:22.540 --> 00:26:24.584
East side. clear.

509
00:26:24.668 --> 00:26:26.712
I'll be the bait. I've
got Dee's vehicle.

510
00:26:26.795 --> 00:26:28.129
I'll park it as
central as I can.

511
00:26:28.296 --> 00:26:30.215
Well. he's expecting
a male. Black. right?

512
00:26:30.298 --> 00:26:32.634
Shouldn't I be the bait?
-Nah.

513
00:26:32.717 --> 00:26:34.135
Why not? That's safer.

514
00:26:34.302 --> 00:26:36.888
Who the hell cares?
It's my case. my target.

515
00:26:39.474 --> 00:26:40.558
Okay.

516
00:26:45.563 --> 00:26:48.024
I got something... coming
in from the south end.

517
00:26:48.108 --> 00:26:49.859
Anybody seeing this?

518
00:26:55.198 --> 00:26:56.700
Yeah. I got him.

519
00:26:56.783 --> 00:26:58.576
He's coming right towards you.

520
00:27:01.663 --> 00:27:02.580
Is it Raptor?

521
00:27:06.042 --> 00:27:07.836
Dee?

522
00:27:07.961 --> 00:27:09.087
Crash.

523
00:27:14.634 --> 00:27:16.553
Dee. what's going on?

524
00:27:16.636 --> 00:27:18.472
-Chicago PD!
-Get down!

525
00:27:18.555 --> 00:27:20.182
-Hands in the air. now!
-Wait. wait. wait. wait!

526
00:27:20.265 --> 00:27:22.392
Turn around! Turn around!
Get on the ground right now!

527
00:27:22.475 --> 00:27:24.144
-Okay.
-Get down!

528
00:27:24.227 --> 00:27:26.604
Hands down! Hands
wide. Keep 'em wide.

529
00:27:29.649 --> 00:27:31.609
Who the hell are you?

530
00:27:31.693 --> 00:27:34.613
How do you know the name Dee?

531
00:27:34.696 --> 00:27:36.614
Oh. my God.

532
00:27:40.882 --> 00:27:43.346
Come on! Let's go! Go!

533
00:27:43.610 --> 00:27:47.155
-Stay down! Down!
-Stay there. Stay low.

534
00:27:47.391 --> 00:27:49.560
Can we see where
those are coming from?

535
00:27:49.644 --> 00:27:51.145
No. I can't see!
I don't have eyes!

536
00:27:53.403 --> 00:27:55.197
All right. I got
him... one o'clock.

537
00:27:55.281 --> 00:27:56.824
Kev. I'm moving.
-I got you. I'ma cover you.

538
00:28:01.626 --> 00:28:02.836
You got eyes on the shooter?

539
00:28:02.920 --> 00:28:05.047
12 o'clock in that
abandoned structure.

540
00:28:05.139 --> 00:28:07.142
Hey. who sent you here?

541
00:28:07.226 --> 00:28:08.246
No one. no one.

542
00:28:08.330 --> 00:28:10.415
-Answer me. Who sent you?
-I don't know.

543
00:28:10.499 --> 00:28:12.460
Yes. you do. Who?

544
00:28:12.647 --> 00:28:14.440
I don't know.
I-i-it was some guy.

545
00:28:14.630 --> 00:28:16.508
He found me in the
alleyway. I was shooting up.

546
00:28:16.598 --> 00:28:18.683
He promised me $400
if I came here.

547
00:28:18.767 --> 00:28:20.518
Describe him.

548
00:28:22.869 --> 00:28:24.996
He's moving. Let's go. let's go.

549
00:28:29.209 --> 00:28:30.752
He was just shooting at you.

550
00:28:30.835 --> 00:28:33.255
Those bullets were
for you. you hear me?

551
00:28:33.338 --> 00:28:35.131
Now describe him.

552
00:28:35.215 --> 00:28:37.884
It was... it was a Black
guy in his mid-30s.

553
00:28:37.967 --> 00:28:39.803
-He drive a car?
-Yeah.

554
00:28:39.886 --> 00:28:42.055
Yeah. but... but he... he
parked in the alleyway.

555
00:28:42.138 --> 00:28:44.600
It was... it was
a dark-blue car.

556
00:28:44.683 --> 00:28:47.018
Which alley?

557
00:29:01.282 --> 00:29:04.285
You see those plates?

558
00:29:05.912 --> 00:29:07.372
No.

559
00:29:11.918 --> 00:29:14.755
Getting the cams sent
over from OCD Tech.

560
00:29:14.838 --> 00:29:17.007
-You got Downey?
-No. Jones. He's better.

561
00:29:17.090 --> 00:29:19.426
And he owes me more.
-Mm.

562
00:29:19.509 --> 00:29:22.053
Hey. concentrate on the
back west-side alley.

563
00:29:22.137 --> 00:29:23.513
If he was shooting
up back there...

564
00:29:23.596 --> 00:29:25.140
All right. two
perps on the east.

565
00:29:25.223 --> 00:29:26.642
Y'all work real well together.

566
00:29:26.725 --> 00:29:28.727
You're not really saying
that like it's a good thing.

567
00:29:28.810 --> 00:29:31.271
Mm. real. uh.
"Brady Bunch" vibe.

568
00:29:33.106 --> 00:29:34.691
Still no investigative alerts.

569
00:29:34.774 --> 00:29:36.526
The ATF's still
working the scene.

570
00:29:36.609 --> 00:29:38.820
All right. I got it.

571
00:29:38.945 --> 00:29:41.907
Hey. that's him. That's our guy.

572
00:29:41.990 --> 00:29:43.992
-Can you enhance it?
-Go.

573
00:29:45.910 --> 00:29:48.413
All right. King Seven Paul 561.

574
00:29:50.749 --> 00:29:52.917
Wait. this car is registered
to a Clark Marten...

575
00:29:53.001 --> 00:29:55.295
no criminal history.
white male. 56 years old.

576
00:29:55.420 --> 00:29:56.838
lives in Park Ridge.

577
00:29:56.921 --> 00:29:58.757
Definitely dummy plates.
-Could be a known associate?

578
00:29:58.840 --> 00:29:59.924
That's an alias.

579
00:30:00.008 --> 00:30:01.301
This dude has a
property in his name...

580
00:30:01.384 --> 00:30:03.303
a defunct garage
in deep Lawndale.

581
00:30:03.386 --> 00:30:05.388
You think our white
56-year-old. Clark Marten.

582
00:30:05.472 --> 00:30:07.140
actually owns that building?
-Let's hit it.

583
00:30:07.223 --> 00:30:09.351
Imani. call your supervisor.

584
00:30:09.476 --> 00:30:11.394
Or we get it ourselves.

585
00:30:11.478 --> 00:30:13.105
Look. if I'm Raptor.
I got my bags packed.

586
00:30:13.188 --> 00:30:14.898
pieces stashed. and I'm
heading out of town.

587
00:30:14.981 --> 00:30:16.525
Trust me. we do not have time

588
00:30:16.608 --> 00:30:18.443
for what my bosses will insist
on... we should hit it. now.

589
00:30:18.526 --> 00:30:20.612
Kev. Adam. you got to
go back to your beats.

590
00:30:20.695 --> 00:30:22.030
-No.
-No.

591
00:30:22.113 --> 00:30:24.032
-No. no way. boss.
-Look. we got this.

592
00:30:24.115 --> 00:30:27.243
Go work 'em.

593
00:32:32.327 --> 00:32:33.912
I got something.

594
00:32:37.582 --> 00:32:39.501
This idiot registered
his laptop.

595
00:32:41.461 --> 00:32:44.297
I got his cell phone
number. We can ping it.

596
00:32:51.065 --> 00:32:52.904
He's headed westbound.

597
00:32:53.120 --> 00:32:56.247
No. ATF's securing his stash.
We're following Raptor now.

598
00:32:56.331 --> 00:32:57.958
Like I said. he's a flight risk.

599
00:32:58.042 --> 00:33:00.038
I've been working this
guy a month... I know him.

600
00:33:00.122 --> 00:33:02.875
He's going to get the
hell out of Chicago.

601
00:33:03.344 --> 00:33:06.222
No. I'm watching him right
now. He's headed for 290.

602
00:33:06.306 --> 00:33:07.974
Boss. he's going to get...

603
00:33:08.058 --> 00:33:11.311
What? No. Why the
hell would we do that?

604
00:33:11.395 --> 00:33:13.660
No. I'm telling
you. that's a bad...

605
00:33:18.331 --> 00:33:19.875
Right.

606
00:33:19.958 --> 00:33:22.002
Mm-hmm. Yep.

607
00:33:22.085 --> 00:33:23.295
Okay.

608
00:33:23.378 --> 00:33:25.046
I'll hold anchor
when we get eyes.

609
00:33:27.132 --> 00:33:28.550
Am I slowing down?

610
00:33:31.094 --> 00:33:32.094
No.

611
00:33:36.182 --> 00:33:37.726
He's moving on to Cermak.

612
00:33:44.441 --> 00:33:46.318
There. 12 o'clock. 2
cars' length ahead of us.

613
00:33:46.401 --> 00:33:48.445
Yeah. I see him.

614
00:33:50.822 --> 00:33:52.741
You got eyes on the driver?

615
00:33:52.866 --> 00:33:54.659
Yeah. that's him. That's Raptor.

616
00:34:04.044 --> 00:34:06.338
-You good?
-Go.

617
00:34:13.720 --> 00:34:16.014
Police! Hands where
I can see them!

618
00:34:16.097 --> 00:34:18.183
Chicago PD! Let
me see your hands!

619
00:34:18.266 --> 00:34:19.851
-Gun!
-Get out of the vehicle!

620
00:34:25.565 --> 00:34:27.651
Put your hands on the wheel.

621
00:34:27.734 --> 00:34:29.486
I don't repeat myself.

622
00:34:39.496 --> 00:34:42.582
12 long guns. 6 Glocks.
4 with switches.

623
00:34:42.665 --> 00:34:44.709
And that Draco was
a match for the gun

624
00:34:44.793 --> 00:34:46.545
that killed Kenton and Aggie.
-Mm.

625
00:34:46.628 --> 00:34:49.673
Also had a packed
bag. 30 thou in cash.

626
00:34:49.756 --> 00:34:52.133
He was going to skip town.
-Mm-hmm.

627
00:34:58.515 --> 00:35:01.310
You need to take box
one on the arrest.

628
00:35:01.393 --> 00:35:03.937
If you don't own him. ATF
will cut Raptor a deal.

629
00:35:04.104 --> 00:35:05.980
My supervisor
wants his contacts.

630
00:35:06.064 --> 00:35:08.233
He doesn't care if the man's
guns have killed 23 people.

631
00:35:08.316 --> 00:35:10.235
He wouldn't know
their names and face

632
00:35:10.318 --> 00:35:11.986
if they walked up to
him and spit on him.

633
00:35:12.070 --> 00:35:13.488
You can't give me box one.

634
00:35:13.613 --> 00:35:15.407
You will get your
ass handed to you.

635
00:35:15.490 --> 00:35:16.991
I don't care.

636
00:35:17.075 --> 00:35:19.077
23. all right?

637
00:35:19.160 --> 00:35:20.537
That man does not
deserve a deal.

638
00:35:20.620 --> 00:35:21.955
He deserves life inside.

639
00:35:22.122 --> 00:35:24.582
and I don't care
who gives it to him.

640
00:35:30.505 --> 00:35:32.841
Can you help me with something?

641
00:35:36.469 --> 00:35:37.846
I did everything you asked.

642
00:35:37.929 --> 00:35:39.806
No. no. no. I don't got
time for this tonight.

643
00:35:39.889 --> 00:35:42.059
I worked Rapid Response.

644
00:35:42.142 --> 00:35:43.977
My team of elite officers.

645
00:35:44.060 --> 00:35:47.147
they worked dead-end
patrol for a month.

646
00:35:47.230 --> 00:35:49.066
I don't
got any new answers.

647
00:35:49.149 --> 00:35:53.319
When they could have been
working real cases. like today.

648
00:35:53.486 --> 00:35:56.031
My team has the
highest solve rate

649
00:35:56.114 --> 00:35:58.158
in the city.

650
00:35:58.241 --> 00:35:59.659
Sir.

651
00:36:01.536 --> 00:36:03.663
Please.

652
00:36:03.747 --> 00:36:05.832
Sign my unit back.

653
00:36:08.084 --> 00:36:10.545
No boss with an
ounce of self-regard

654
00:36:10.670 --> 00:36:12.839
would sign your
unit back together.

655
00:36:12.922 --> 00:36:14.507
not when your unit

656
00:36:14.591 --> 00:36:17.552
destroys everyone it touches.

657
00:36:17.719 --> 00:36:21.598
I'm not signing
Intelligence back...

658
00:36:21.681 --> 00:36:23.683
ever.

659
00:36:33.818 --> 00:36:36.738
I tried to do this
the right way.

660
00:36:38.740 --> 00:36:41.409
-What's this?
-I really did.

661
00:36:41.534 --> 00:36:42.827
Open it.

662
00:36:45.330 --> 00:36:49.000
ATF is still tracking every
gun from Raptor's stash.

663
00:36:49.084 --> 00:36:51.169
I mean. he had boxes
from gun shows.

664
00:36:51.252 --> 00:36:55.757
manufacturers. gun stores
all across the U.S.

665
00:36:55.840 --> 00:36:59.177
Those are the ones I asked
ATF to prioritize. though.

666
00:37:01.805 --> 00:37:03.139
You recognize 'em.

667
00:37:08.395 --> 00:37:11.606
Serial numbers all
trace back to the CPD.

668
00:37:11.773 --> 00:37:14.234
It was a batch of
weapons that IAD ordered

669
00:37:14.359 --> 00:37:16.737
to replenish their officers...

670
00:37:16.820 --> 00:37:20.282
same batch that your
predecessors and you

671
00:37:20.365 --> 00:37:23.160
signed off on...

672
00:37:23.243 --> 00:37:24.869
and never reported stolen.

673
00:37:28.498 --> 00:37:31.543
I mean. I doubt you
know who stole 'em.

674
00:37:33.420 --> 00:37:35.547
It was just an
embarrassment. right?

675
00:37:39.801 --> 00:37:43.388
It went against your
self-preservation to report it.

676
00:37:46.016 --> 00:37:48.893
I mean. think how
pathetic it'll look now.

677
00:37:51.646 --> 00:37:55.734
My unit is reinstated tonight...

678
00:37:55.900 --> 00:37:58.570
or this goes public.

679
00:38:11.458 --> 00:38:15.086
You can't outrun
yourself forever. Hank.

680
00:38:39.235 --> 00:38:41.071
Wow.

681
00:38:41.154 --> 00:38:43.907
Really beautiful space.

682
00:38:43.990 --> 00:38:46.743
You talk to your supervisor?

683
00:38:46.826 --> 00:38:48.537
Why'd you want to meet here?

684
00:38:48.620 --> 00:38:51.456
Is that a tic of yours?
You don't answer questions?

685
00:38:51.539 --> 00:38:53.333
Well. you don't either. right?

686
00:38:53.416 --> 00:38:56.795
You're not exactly a
shining conversationalist.

687
00:38:56.961 --> 00:38:59.255
What'd he give you?

688
00:38:59.339 --> 00:39:00.924
Early end to my detail.

689
00:39:01.091 --> 00:39:02.759
-Huh.
-Yeah.

690
00:39:02.842 --> 00:39:05.387
It's fine. I was feeling like
it was time to pack up anyway.

691
00:39:05.470 --> 00:39:07.180
move somewhere else.

692
00:39:07.263 --> 00:39:09.391
I don't really like to
stay put for too long.

693
00:39:09.474 --> 00:39:11.017
I can tell.

694
00:39:14.229 --> 00:39:16.773
Plus. that boss
was a damn idiot.

695
00:39:16.856 --> 00:39:18.400
Hmm.

696
00:39:18.483 --> 00:39:20.944
Moved like a slug and
couldn't see jack coming.

697
00:39:21.027 --> 00:39:23.238
The world could be
ending. and he'd be like.

698
00:39:23.321 --> 00:39:25.490
what's the weather like. and
what jacket should I pack?

699
00:39:27.242 --> 00:39:29.453
So you're gonna outrun
the consequences.

700
00:39:29.536 --> 00:39:31.955
Yeah. I'm gonna try.

701
00:39:32.038 --> 00:39:34.165
What were their names?

702
00:39:34.249 --> 00:39:35.834
What?

703
00:39:35.959 --> 00:39:39.129
The six who were killed by
Raptor's guns in Chicago...

704
00:39:39.212 --> 00:39:41.589
what were their names?

705
00:39:45.510 --> 00:39:48.472
George Malkin. Javon Dyer.

706
00:39:48.555 --> 00:39:52.934
Anthony Rodriguez.
Cattie Rodriguez.

707
00:39:53.101 --> 00:39:55.854
Kenton Williams. and
Aggie Montgomery.

708
00:40:04.487 --> 00:40:07.198
Why don't you run
with us for a while?

709
00:40:10.118 --> 00:40:11.703
You got your unit back?

710
00:40:13.830 --> 00:40:15.707
Got an open spot.

711
00:40:18.668 --> 00:40:21.255
Yeah. that's... that's
a terrible idea.

712
00:40:21.338 --> 00:40:23.465
Hmm.

713
00:40:23.548 --> 00:40:25.467
Why's that?

714
00:40:27.552 --> 00:40:29.429
You don't want me.

715
00:40:31.514 --> 00:40:33.892
I'm not gonna convince
you. It's yes or no.

716
00:40:36.895 --> 00:40:38.897
I'll give you a long leash.

717
00:40:48.114 --> 00:40:49.741
Okay.

718
00:40:52.243 --> 00:40:53.870
Just for a while?

719
00:41:13.181 --> 00:41:15.433
Let's get back to work.

719
00:41:16.305 --> 00:42:16.258
